{"id":89160,"title":"Neglected patellar tendon rupture with anterior cruciate ligament rupture and medial collateral ligament partial rupture.","abstract":"Anterior cruciate ligament injuries are common, mostly occurring during sports trauma. Conversely, patellar tendon ruptures are uncommon injuries secondary to forceful contractions of the extensor mechanism. It is important to consider the possibility of combined injuries around the knee. We present a case of neglected patellar tendon rupture with anterior cruciate ligament and medial collateral ligament rupture treated with arthroscopic anterior cruciate ligament reconstruction combined with patellar tendon reconstruction.","date":"2014-04-21","categories":"Wounds and Injuries","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24747636","annotations":[{"name":"Anterior cruciate ligament","weight":0.900148,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anterior_cruciate_ligament"},{"name":"Medial collateral ligament","weight":0.888095,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medial_collateral_ligament"},{"name":"Patellar ligament","weight":0.865084,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patellar_ligament"},{"name":"Ligament","weight":0.749237,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ligament"},{"name":"Knee","weight":0.748506,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Knee"},{"name":"Patella","weight":0.741322,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patella"},{"name":"Tendon","weight":0.73528,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tendon"},{"name":"Anterior cruciate ligament reconstruction","weight":0.705309,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anterior_cruciate_ligament_reconstruction"},{"name":"Cruciate ligament","weight":0.698738,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cruciate_ligament"},{"name":"Arthroscopy","weight":0.669175,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arthroscopy"},{"name":"Extension (kinesiology)","weight":0.660386,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Extension_(kinesiology)"},{"name":"Trauma (medicine)","weight":0.514344,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trauma_(medicine)"},{"name":"Muscle contraction","weight":0.43934,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muscle_contraction"},{"name":"Anatomical terms of location","weight":0.305365,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anatomical_terms_of_location"},{"name":"Sprain","weight":0.054746,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sprain"},{"name":"Sport","weight":0.0391252,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sport"},{"name":"Anterior","weight":0.0339747,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anterior"},{"name":"Tendinosis","weight":0.0300804,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tendinosis"},{"name":"Patellar tendon rupture","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patellar_tendon_rupture"},{"name":"Defensive back","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Defensive_back"},{"name":"Collateral (finance)","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Collateral_(finance)"}]}
